      "content": "That's a fair point about the historical context. Following that logic, if we were looking at a quantitative predictive model for real estate, would it be considered more \"accurate\" or \"data-driven\" to include racial demographic trends as a negative coefficient for predicting property value retention? Or is there a way to model that stability without relying on those specific demographic variables?",
